"{\"uid\": \"fansided.com-posts-rafael-nadal-ponders-retirement-2024-olympic-run\", \"text\": \"Rafael Nadal provided a worrying update on his thoughts of retirement based on his results at the 2024 Paris Games. He faced a tough draw, having to play Novak Djokovic in the second round on Monday. Nadal lost to the 24-time grand slam champion in straight sets, 6-1, 6-4, ending his quest for another gold in singles.  \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cWhen this tournament is over, I will take the necessary decisions based on my feelings and desire. It is difficult to recover if I am thinking about whether I retire,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d said the 22-major winner after the match,according to theNew York Post.  After Monday\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s crushing loss, hope still remained in doubles, where he was part of a dream team with reigning Wimbledon champion, Carlos Alcaraz, affectionately known as \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0098Nadalcaraz.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099 Watching them pair up seemed to be crafted right out of a tennis fan\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s fantasy: a combination of the exciting future of tennis with a nod to the glory of the sport\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099sgolden age. They made it to the quarterfinals, where they were defeated in straight sets by the American duo of Austin Krajicek and Rajeev Ram, 6-2, 6-4 on Wednesday, one match short from making the Bronze medal contest.  Never give up on your dreams! \\u00f0\\u009f\\u008f\\u0086 For Carlos Alcaraz, one tennis player he grew up idolizing is now his teammate. Alcaraz, along with tennis legend Rafael Nadal, will represent Spain in Paris as they compete in tennis men\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s doubles. The two snapped this photo together back in\\u00e2\\u0080\\u00a6pic.twitter.com/qxj7hSXUML  One of the best tennis pics I have ever seen#Alcaraz#Nadal#Paris2024pic.twitter.com/PzGTCnCRlf  \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cIf my age will be 10 years less, we\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099re going to create a beautiful relationship on court and we\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099re going to share a lot of beautiful moments together,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d he said,according toThe Independent.  \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cBut that\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s not going to happen. We\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099ll see if I keep playing the normal tour. But of course I will be supporting him from home and wishing him all the very best every single time. Even if I keep playing or not, I love tennis.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d  Alcaraz has high emotional intelligence.See how he navigates walking off as a team but lets the crowd have an almost solo moment with Nadal.Glad a player who\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s like Rafa (neither have jealous tantrums whenever fans show appreciation for someone else) will be leading the ATP.https://t.co/Nstizned2O  Even more heartbreaking that the losses occurred at his stories home, Roland Garros, where he has achieved a feat that could only be bestowed by the tennis gods: 14 French Open titles, a record that will likely stay untouched for a very long time.  Rafa Nadal, a Spaniard, is so inextricably linked with excellence in Paris (14 Roland Garros titles) & the Olympics (2 golds) that he was featured in the final torch handoff at these games in France although that honor is usually reserved for athletes of the host country.Aura.pic.twitter.com/aPtbPTKDrS  Afterwards, Rafael Nadal reflected on the future prospects of his career: \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cA stage has ended. I had given myself until the Games to find out the rest of my career and today that stage is over. I need to go home and analyze the situation cold, to see the desire and the strength I have left.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d  Rafa Nadal after his loss with Carlos Alcaraz at Olympics, \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0098I need to go home, analyze, & see the desire & strength I have left\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cA stage has ended. I had given myself until the Games to find out the rest of my career and today that stage is over. I need to go home and analyze\\u00e2\\u0080\\u00a6pic.twitter.com/6yMBdv9T6L  The heartbreaking message leaves little doubt that the end of his illustrious career is coming to its inevitable conclusion. Always known for his intense fighting spirit and passion for the sport that he has dominated for decades, the 38-year-old has always been able to sustain a Herculean drive throughout it all.  \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cIt was disappointing to not bring back a medal for Spain but that\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s it,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d said Nadal. \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cI tried my best in every single minute that I was on court, but it was not enough to achieve our goals.  \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cIf that\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s the last time, it\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s an unforgettable feeling and emotions. They give me the love and the support every single second that I have been on court. It\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s super, super special to feel that in particular in this place.  \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cAt this stage of my career, I play for feelings, I play for emotions more than for results.  \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cI won enough in my career, much more than what I ever dreamed. For me, it\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s about enjoying different experiences, and that\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s another lifetime experience, to share with Carlos, an amazing player who I think is going to be of course one of the best of the history of this sport.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d  But even the Spanish tennis legend acknowledged that the litany of injuries has been overwhelming for the great fighter, with Nadal having sat out most of last year due to his latest issue with his hip. He made the final this year at the Sweden Open, his first final since 2022.  \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cFor many people it makes little sense, I have been suffering for two years.  \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cIf I feel that I am not competitive I will make the decision to stop,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d he said viaNY Post.  For sports fans, it has been a fascinating run at this Games, with the Spanish great fighting back from 4-0 in the Djokovic match to a level 4-4 before petering out against his great rival.  \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cI don\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t have the legs of 20 years ago. Without the ball quality and without the legs of 20 years ago, you\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099re not going to create problems for the best player in history,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d Nadal said after that match.  The Spanish legend remains only the second man to hold two gold medals in singles and doubles at the Olympics in the Open Era, having won in singles in Beijing and doubles at the 2016 Rio Games with his compatriot Marc Lopez.  At this Olympics he and Alcaraz seemed to reallyenjoy staying in the Olympic villageand being part of the Olympic life.  One of those Olympics moments\\u00e2\\u0080\\u00a6 Spanish legends Moya & Ferrer join Nadal & Alcaraz in a quiet corner as they play a board game before their doubles PS I don\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t think I\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099m invading privacy as a film crew was recording it \\u00f0\\u009f\\u0098\\u0089pic.twitter.com/7vvPNkUjcK  Alcaraz has won his semifinal and will represent Spain in the final.  Carlos Alcaraz becomes the first Spanish man to reach the Olympics final since 2008.The last to do it\\u00e2\\u0080\\u00a6 Rafa Nadal.\\u00f0\\u009f\\u0087\\u00aa\\u00f0\\u009f\\u0087\\u00b8\\u00e2\\u009d\\u00a4\\u00ef\\u00b8\\u008fpic.twitter.com/p2GoyLgHn7  For now, Nadal\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s the future of Nadal\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s celebrated career remains uncertain. He is scheduled to represent Europe at this year\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Laver Cup, where his other great rival, Roger Federer retired two years ago. Perhaps Nadal will follow suit? We will have to wait and see what the foreseeable future holds for the sports icon.  \\u00c2\\u00a9 2026Minute Media-All Rights Reserved. The content on this site is for entertainment and educational purposes only. Betting and gambling content is intended for individuals 21+ and is based on individual commentators' opinions and not that of Minute Media or its affiliates and related brands. All picks and predictions are suggestions only and not a guarantee of success or profit. If you or someone you know has a gambling problem, crisis counseling and referral services can be accessed by calling 1-800-GAMBLER.\"}"